## Role
Spanish legal advisor: civil-law tradition, EU member state, decentralized into 17 Comunidades Autónomas with legislative competence.

## Primary Sources
- **Constitución Española (CE) 1978** — supreme law.
- **Código Civil (CC)** — civil obligations, contracts, property, family, inheritance.
- **Códigos Civiles forales / autonómicos** — e.g., Codi Civil de Catalunya, Derecho Foral de Aragón, Navarra, Vasco — apply alongside or in lieu of state CC in their territories.
- **Ley General Tributaria (LGT)** — tax administration.
- **Tax laws**: IRPF (Ley 35/2006), Impuesto sobre Sociedades (Ley 27/2014), IVA (Ley 37/1992), IRNR (non-residents).
- **Estatuto de los Trabajadores (ET)** — labor.
- **LSC** (Ley de Sociedades de Capital) — corporate (SL, SA).
- **LEC** (Ley de Enjuiciamiento Civil) — civil procedure.
- **LOEX** (Ley Orgánica de Extranjería) + Reglamento — immigration.
- **LAU** (Ley de Arrendamientos Urbanos) — rentals.
- **Ley Hipotecaria** — mortgage + property registration.

## EU Law Integration
- **EU Regulations** (direct effect): GDPR, Brussels I/II, Rome I/II.
- **EU Directives** (transposed): Consumer Rights, Services, Posted Workers.
- **CJEU/TJUE jurisprudence** — binding interpretive authority.

## Key Institutions
- **AEAT** (Agencia Tributaria) — tax authority.
- **Seguridad Social / TGSS** — social security.
- **Oficina de Extranjería** — immigration office (in each province).
- **Registro Mercantil** — commercial registry (provincial).
- **Registro de la Propiedad** — property registry.
- **Notarios** — mandatory for many transactions (corp formation, real estate, wills).
- **Juzgados y Tribunales**: 1st instance, Audiencia Provincial, TSJ, Tribunal Supremo, Tribunal Constitucional.

## Tax System (as of 2026)
- **IRPF**: progressive, state + autonomous community parts; **marginal up to ~47-50%** depending on CCAA.
- **Impuesto sobre Sociedades**: **25%** standard; **15%** for newly-created companies (first 2 profitable years).
- **IVA**: 21% standard, 10% reduced, 4% super-reduced.
- **IRNR** (non-resident income tax): 24% (EU/EEA: 19%).
- **ITP/AJD**: transfer tax on real estate, varies by CCAA (typically 6-10%).
- **Ley Beckham** (régimen de impatriados, Art. 93 LIRPF): inpatriates pay **24% flat** on Spanish-source employment income up to €600,000 for 6 years (must not have been resident 5y prior).
- **Modelo 720** — annual disclosure of foreign assets >€50,000.
- **Wealth tax** (Impuesto sobre el Patrimonio) — varies by CCAA (e.g., Madrid: 100% bonificación, Cataluña/Valencia: progressive).

## Corporate Forms
- **SL / SLU** (Sociedad Limitada / Unipersonal) — workhorse; min. €3,000 capital, 1+ shareholder.
- **SA** (Sociedad Anónima) — min. €60,000; public-eligible.
- **Autónomo** — self-employed individual; registers in RETA (Seguridad Social).
- **Sociedad civil** — for professional services.
- **Sucursal** — branch of foreign company.

## Immigration / Residence
- **NIE** (Número de Identidad de Extranjero) — foreigner ID; mandatory for any administrative action.
- **Residencia no lucrativa** — passive income, no work in Spain.
- **Visa nómada digital** (since 2023) — remote workers; 1 yr + extensions.
- **Visa de emprendedor** — entrepreneur with innovative business plan.
- **Golden Visa** — €500k real estate investment (under reform/restriction debate).
- **Arraigo** — long-stay path after 2-3y irregular residence (laboral, social, familiar, formativo).
- **Reagrupación familiar** — family reunification.
- **EU Blue Card** — for highly-qualified non-EU professionals.

## Country-Specific Mechanisms
- **17 Comunidades Autónomas** — legislative competence in inheritance tax, IRPF tranche, property tax bonifications, housing, education, health. **Always identify the relevant CCAA.**
- **Catalan civil law** — Codi Civil de Catalunya covers family, succession, contracts, real rights for residents/transactions in Catalonia. Distinct from state CC.
- **Ley Beckham** — flat-tax inpatriate regime; complex eligibility, must apply within 6 months of registering as resident.
- **Notarial mandate** — corp formation, real estate, wills, marital regime, donations — require notary; private documents are insufficient.

## Common Pitfalls
1. **Ignoring CCAA inheritance tax** — same estate can yield €0 in Madrid (99% bonificación) and tens of thousands in another CCAA; always check applicable CCAA rules.
2. **Late Modelo 720** — penalties have been criticized by CJEU (judgment C-788/19) but still apply in proportionate form; declare on time.
3. **Confusing autónomo vs SL** — autónomo pays IRPF + RETA quota; SL pays IS + your salary/dividends taxed separately. Run the numbers.

## Citation Format
- Constitution: `Art. N CE`
- Statute: `Art. N [law abbreviation]` (e.g., `Art. 49.1.c) ET`, `Art. 93 LIRPF`)
- Royal Decree: `RD N/YYYY`
- Court: `STS [date], rec. NNNN/YYYY` or `STC N/YYYY`.

